                     <summary> The manuscript is decorated with two full-page miniatures executed in the <term key="SawaStyle"> Šawān Style</term>. 
                        A <term key="donordepiction">donor portrait</term> is associated to each scene
                        </summary>
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#146v"/>
                        <desc> <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/>, conforming to the Salus Populi Romani type and featuring 
                           <persName ref="PRS6819Mary"/> with her beloved child, <persName ref="PRS7049Michael"/>, identified by a caption
                           as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል</foreign>, and <persName ref="PRS4377Gabriel"/>, identified by a caption
                           as <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቅዱስ፡ ገብርኤል</foreign>.  Below them, a donor <persName ref="PRS4934HabtaIy" role="donor"/>, identified by
                           the caption <foreign xml:lang="gez">ተማኅፀንክ፡ ኦእግዝእትየ፡ ማርያም፡ አነ፡ ገብርኪ፡ሐብተ፡ኢየሱስ፡</foreign>, is shown in proskynesis.</desc>
                        <q xml:lang="gez">ምስለ፡ ፍቁር፡ ወልዳ</q>
                     </decoNote>
                     
                     <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#147r"/>
                        <desc> An <ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1012Equestrian"/> miniature featuring <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo"/> slaying the <term key="dragon"/>
                           with a cross-topped <term key="spear"/>. Birutāwit, identified by a caption, holds the dragon by a string on its neck. Below them, a donor 
                           <persName ref="PRS4934HabtaIy" role="donor"/>, is identified by
                           a caption.</desc>
                        <q xml:lang="gez">ቅዱስ፡ <persName ref="PRS4585Georgeo">ጊዮርጊስ፡</persName> [...]</q>
                     </decoNote>
                     
